{"word":"H6942 - קָדַשׁ - qâdash - kaw-dash' - Appoint","slug":"H6942","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">קָדַשׁ</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>qâdash"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>kaw-dash'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Appoint"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E7;&#x05D3;&#x05E9;&#x05C1; - qa&#x0302;dash</b> - <i>kaw-dash'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>be</i> (causatively <i>make</i>, <i>pronounce</i> or <i>observe</i> as) <i>clean</i> (ceremonially or morally): - appoint, bid, consecrate, dedicate, defile, hallow, (be, keep) holy (-er, place), keep, prepare, proclaim, purify, sanctify (-ied one, self), X wholly."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H4720\">H4720</a>, <a href=\"#/H6918\">H6918</a>, <a href=\"#/H6943\">H6943</a>, <a href=\"#/H6944\">H6944</a>, <a href=\"#/H6945\">H6945</a>, <a href=\"#/H6946\">H6946</a>, <a href=\"#/H6947\">H6947</a>, <a href=\"#/H6948\">H6948</a>"}]}